Lipase activity was inferred by measuring p-nitrophenyl butyrate (PNPB) degradation rates at 400 nm. Cultures were grown for 16 h as described above, in a modified version of mLB to which 0.5% tributyrin was added before inoculation. Culture supernatants were recovered by centrifugation, and 100 μl volumeswere resuspended in 900 µl reaction buffer (100 mM NaH2PO4, 150 mM NaCl, 0.5% (v/v) Triton X-100, pH 7.2). 10 µl of 50 mM PNPB was added and the absorbance (400 nm) measured every 30 s for 5 min at 60 °C. Solution containing the reaction buffer, non-inoculated media and PNPB were used as negative controls. All measurements were performed in triplicates. The rate of PNPB degradation in units/ml enzyme was determined using the following equation:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
